This project (Orin) is a CI/CD tool for automating update server-side's services.

It requires a valid JDK installation(JDK 22 or above) to run, and in most cases, a valid network port is required for Github webhooks.

Current minimal workflow support:
- `POST /webhook` or `POST /webhook/github` accepts a GitHub push payload and dispatches matching pipelines.
- `POST /trigger/{pipeline}` triggers a configured pipeline manually. Request body can be empty or:
  `{"token":"change-me","inputs":{"branch":"main"}}`
- Pipelines reference actions by name, and each action is loaded from `actions/<name>/entry.toml`.
- Action entry can be either `.kts` or `.sh`.
- KTS actions receive a restricted read-only `context` plus a small `orin` API.

Example action layout:
`actions/github-push-summary/entry.toml`
`actions/github-push-summary/main.kts`
`actions/build-shell/entry.toml`
`actions/build-shell/main.sh`

For it's old GoLang implementation, see https://github.com/glowingstone124/GoCi.

Its name was inspired from Kaenbyou Rin, a character from Touhou Project.

